Package com.b2international.commons.hierarchy

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Ancestor<E>
    Represents a hierarchical element that holds parentage information about its descendants based on any kind of logical classification.
    Derivation<E extends HierarchicalElement<E>>
    Represents a derivation of hierarchical elements.
    Descendant<E>
    Represents a hierarchical element that holds parentage information about its direct ancestor based on any kind of logical classification.
    HierarchicalElement<E>
    Represents a hierarchical component aggregating an ancestor and a descendant.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EntryToKeyFunction<T>  
    EntryValuePredicate<T>  
    Hierarchy<M>
    Simple editable hierarchical structure where: Each member may be added only once. Each member may have arbitrary number of children or no child at all. Each member may have exactly one parent or no parent at all.
    PreorderIterator<E extends Ancestor<E>>
    Iterator for traversing a derivation on Ancestor instances in pre-order fashion.
